    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a731c563_88c6abce",
        "filename": "src/gpu/GrGpu.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 14
      },
      "lineNbr": 295,
      "author": {
        "id": 5085
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-02-16T19:28:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m not sure we can make a determination here since we don\u0027t know whether the src data is srgb encoded. The caller told us not to do a conversion. We\u0027re not introducing a draw at this level, so unless the subclass introduces a draw no conversion will happen (since GrGpu::writePixels() never does a conversion even if the dst config is GrSRGBEncoded::kYes). Conversions only happen through draws.\n\nThe only way we could accidentally wind up with a conversion is if the subclass causes a draw. So I think the subclass has to guard against creating a converting draw.\n\nIn the future as I understand it we will want to get through here with things like F16 as we\u0027ll have data represented in F16 that *are* sRGB-gamma\u0027ed values and we\u0027ll want them to pass straight through to a GL_SRGB texure without conversion. So I\u0027m not going out of my way from preventing that from happening here.",
      "parentUuid": "6fc1378b_69a5f00e",
      "revId": "1dfd6827aa34f1573d693b54a8793c1996d4d78b",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
