      "writtenOn": "2018-02-16T19:28:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "So what this is trying to do is prevent introducing a conversion when one wasn\u0027t requested so its treating the src as though it has the same sRGBness as the dst.\n\nThat said, I don\u0027t think this is sufficient to guard against interactions of a draw triggered below and a sRGB converting draw initiated by the base class. This should really be doing what is going on in the onGetReadPixelsInfo case where we check inside the initial if() whether to match the dst or the temp\u0027s srgbness.\n\nI\u0027ve made that change here and it the vk version.",
